<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/5133484-mariah"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1300298258i/5133484._UY100_CR16,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/5133484-mariah">Mariah</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I believe that Andersen&apos;s Well is actually a reference from earlier in the book. It is the “receptive, unjudging and silent” place where Ethan can go <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I believe that Andersen's Well is actually a reference from earlier in the book. It is the “receptive, unjudging and silent” place where Ethan can go to speak his thoughts. His special place. (I'm sorry I can't give you a page number, I don't have the book in front of me..."<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
